# Trivy ignore file — every entry here must have a justification comment.
# Do not add entries without review; this file is itself part of the audit trail.
#
# Context: All CVEs below are OS-level packages inherited from the
# python:3.12-slim (Debian 13.6) base image. None of them have a
# "Fixed Version" available yet (Debian has not shipped a patched
# package). The application is a pure Python Flask REST API and does
# not invoke perl, gzip, ncurses, or any util-linux/libblkid tooling
# at runtime — these packages are present only as base-OS dependencies,
# not part of the application's attack surface.
#
# Risk acceptance: Documented and accepted until upstream patches are
# available. Revisit this file whenever the base image is rebuilt /
# on a periodic (monthly) dependency review.

# --- util-linux / libblkid family (CVE-2026-53615) ---
# Integer Overflow in libblkid/src/partitions/dos.c. Affects bsdutils,
# libblkid1, libsmartcols1, libuuid1, util-linux, mount, login.
# App never parses disk partitions or calls blkid. Not reachable.
CVE-2026-53615

# --- gzip (CVE-2026-41992) ---
# Buffer overflow in LZH decompression path. App does not invoke gzip
# directly; only used internally by apt during image build.
CVE-2026-41992

# --- libacl1 (CVE-2026-54369) ---
# Symlink traversal privilege escalation via libacl functions.
# App runs as non-root user and does not use ACL syscalls.
CVE-2026-54369

# --- ncurses family (CVE-2025-69720) ---
# Buffer overflow in ncurses. Affects libncursesw6, libtinfo6,
# ncurses-base, ncurses-bin. App has no terminal UI / TTY interaction.
CVE-2025-69720

# --- perl-base / Perl interpreter (multiple CVEs) ---
# App is Python-only; the Perl interpreter shipped with the Debian
# base image is never executed by this application.
CVE-2026-13221
CVE-2026-42496
CVE-2026-8376
CVE-2026-42497
CVE-2026-48962
CVE-2026-57432
CVE-2026-9538